âœ” Display Route
Â Â â€¢ Shows all stations in order.
Â Â â€¢ For circular routes, last station connects back to the first.

âœ” Navigate Forward / Backward
Â Â â€¢ Move to next or previous station (using doubly linked list).

âœ” Search Station
Â Â â€¢ Check if a station exists on the route.

âœ” Plan Journey
Â Â â€¢ Enter a source and destination, program shows path.

ðŸ—ï¸ How It Works (Core Concepts)

Doubly Linked List: Each node (station) has prev and next pointers, enabling two-way navigation.

Circular Linked List: Last stationâ€™s next points to the first, forming a loop.

Traversal Algorithms: Used for route display and journey planning.

